Paper: hep-th/0109006

Date: 2001-09-02

Title: Lump Scattering on a Torus

Authors: RJ Cova

Comments: 13 pages, including 6 figures

Journal-ref: Eur.Phys.J. B15 (2000) 673-678

Head-on collisions between two solitons in the pure $CP^1$ model on a flattorus are investigated via numerical simulations. The charge-two lumps, writtenout in terms of Weierstrass' elliptic $\wp$-function, are found to scatter at90$^{\circ}$. The phenomenon of singularity formation is also seen.